<p><b>Birth date:</b> October 31, 1984</br>

<b>Education:</b></br>
2002 – 2007 Faculty of Biology, Moscow State University, Russia</br>
2007 – 2010 Postgraduate education, Paleontological Institute, Russian Academy of Sciences</br>
November 2010 Ph.D., Entomology Paleontological Institute, Russian Academy of Sciences</br>

<p><b>Employment history:</b></br>
2002 – 2005 Laboratory assistant, Institute for Theoretical and Experimental Physics</br>
2007 – present Junior scientist, Laboratory of Arthropods, Paleontological Institute</br>
2007 – present Guide, Paleontological Museum, Moscow</br>
2011 – present Scientific Editor, Paleontological Journal, Nauka Publishing House</br>

<p><b>Scientific interests:</b></br>
Fossil Hymenoptera, especially Ichneumonoidea</br>

<p><b>Professional Memberships:</b></br>
Russian Entomological Society</br>


<p><b>PUBLICATIONS</b></br>
<p><b>PhD Thesis</b></br>
Kopylov D.S., 2010. The Early Stages of the Evolution of Ichneumon Flies. Thesis for the degree of Doctor of Philosophy submitted to Russian Academy of Sciences. 157 p. [in Russian, unpubl.]</br>

<p><b>Papers</b></br>
Kopylov D.S., 2009. A New Subfamily of Ichneumonids from the Lower Cretaceous of Transbaikalia and Mongolia (Insecta: Hymenoptera: Ichneuonidae). Paleontological Journal. Vol. 43. No. 1. PP. 83-93.</br>
Kopylov D.S., 2010. Ichneumonids of the Subfamily Tanychorinae (Insecta, Hymenoptera, Ichneumonidae) from the Lower Cretaceous of Transbaikalia and Mongolia. Paleontological Journal. Vol. 44. No. 2. PP. 179-186.</br>
Kopylov D.S., 2010. A New Subfamily of Ichneumon Wasps (Insecta: Hymenoptera: Ichneumonidae) from the Upper Cretaceous of the Russian Far East. Vol. 44. No. 4. PP. 422-433.</br>
Kopylov D.S., Brothers D.J., Rasnitsyn A.P., 2010. Two new labenopimpline ichneumonids (Hymenoptera: Ichneumonidae) from the Upper Cretaceous of southern Africa // African Invertebrates. V. 51(2). P. 423 – 430.</br>





 



